# FilmPilot

A sleek, dark-themed movie discovery web app that uses The Movie Database (TMDb) API to help you browse top-rated, popular, and trending films. FilmPilot includes powerful filters, search, favorites, trailers, and recommendations — all in a responsive interface.

---

## Features

- Browse movies by category: Now Playing, Popular, Top Rated, Upcoming
- Infinite/`Load More` style paging with a friendly load button
- Search movies by title with instant results
- Filters for minimum rating, genre and release year
- Save favorites locally (LocalStorage)
- Play trailers (YouTube) and view recommended movies
- Responsive layout with an expandable sidebar

---

## Tech
- Plain HTML, CSS (custom + Bulma), and vanilla JavaScript
- TMDb (The Movie Database) API for movie data and videos
- No build tools required — static site ready to open in a browser

---

## Getting Started

Prerequisites:

- A modern browser (Chrome, Edge, Firefox, Safari)
- A TMDb API key (free account at https://www.themoviedb.org)

1. Clone or download this repository.
2. Place your TMDb API key into the project:
   - Open `script.js` and set the `API_KEY` constant to your TMDb key:

```js
// in script.js
const API_KEY = 'YOUR_TMDB_API_KEY_HERE';
```

3. Serve the folder with any static file server or open `index.html` directly. For a quick local server you can use your editor's Live Server extension or run:

```powershell
python -m http.server 8000
```

Then open http://localhost:8000 in your browser.

---

## Configuration

- TMDb language is set to `en-US` in API requests. Modify the `fetch` URL in `script.js` if you want a different language.
- Favorites are stored in `localStorage` under the key `favorites`.

---

## Usage

- Use the sidebar to switch categories or open filters.
- Type in the search box to find movies by title.
- Use the star filter, genre, and year selects to refine results.
- Click the heart button on a movie card to add/remove favorites.
- Click "🎬 Trailer" to open a modal with the YouTube trailer (if available).

---

## Contributing

Contributions, issues and feature requests are welcome. For small changes, open a pull request. For larger suggestions, please open an issue first to discuss the change.

---

## Notes & Privacy

- This app stores favorites locally in the browser only — nothing is sent to a server.
- TMDb API usage is subject to TMDb terms and rate limits. Keep your API key private.

